(and in more nations as well), for both genders and for all the five decades of 
life considered. The authors identify the specific causes of excess U.S. 
mortality. Despite huge expenditures for medical care, U.S. citizens have 
embarrassingly high death rates during the prime of life. Nine issues are 
highlighted that may illuminate ways to improve health in the United States.

