PURPOSE: To report successful endovascular repair of thoracic aortic aneurysms 
in 2 patients with human immunodeficiency virus (HIV).
CASE REPORTS: Thoracic and abdominal aortic aneurysms (AAA) were found in a 
60-year-old woman 1 year after she was diagnosed with HIV. Because of pain and 
risk of rupture, the AAA was repaired with conventional open techniques in 
February 1997, while the thoracic aneurysm was excluded in a staged procedure 
